        <updateDate>2016-04-15T20:13:52Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Controlling the Unchecked and Reckless Ballooning of Lifeline Act of 2016 or the CURB Lifeline Act of 2016</b></p> <p>This bill prohibits the total amount of annual support that may be provided through the Lifeline program of the Federal Communications Commission from exceeding $1.5 billion.</p> <p>Support provided through the Lifeline program may not be applied to: (1) any amount charged to a consumer for the sale, lease, or other provision of a mobile telephone or similar device; or (2) mobile service if the service offering is limited to voice communications service.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
